response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Sum of Divisors\", \"description\": \"Given an integer n, write a function sum_of_divisors that calculates the sum of all divisors of n, excluding n itself.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_of_divisors(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A positive integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of all divisors of `n`, excluding `n` itself.\\n\", \"code\": \"def sum_of_divisors(n: int) -> int:\\n    total = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n):\\n        if n % i == 0:\\n            total += i\\n    return total\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_of_divisors(10) == 18\", \"assert sum_of_divisors(12) == 28\", \"assert sum_of_divisors(24) == 30\"] }"
